Reasoning: The paper deals with algorithms for finding the maximum of a function defined on the nodes of a connected graph, which is a problem in graph theory and optimization. The use of local iterative algorithms and probability distributions suggests a focus on algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The convergence rates and simulations suggest a focus on numerical analysis (cs.NA) and statistical inference (cs.SI). The use of descent-based methods suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
